The geodesic distance between two points is the length of the geodesic path connecting them, and it provides a natural measure of distance on the manifold.

The concept of geodesic distance is particularly important in the context of machine learning and data analysis, as it can be used to measure the similarity or dissimilarity between data points in Riemannian manifolds.
